# Frontend (Vite) build-time config. Copy to `.env` only if you need to override a default.
#
# OAuth and the YouTube Data API both go through same-origin Cloudflare Pages Functions
# (/auth/* and /api/*), so the browser holds no Google Client ID or API key. You normally don't
# need any frontend env var at all.
#
# VITE_AUTH_BASE — where the auth Functions are mounted. Defaults to "/auth". Set it to an empty
# string to HIDE the Google sign-in UI (API-key-only deployment). NOTE: this is not a "static"
# build — the /api YouTube proxy + key endpoints are always required, so the Pages Functions must
# be deployed either way. There is no fully static, backend-less deployment.
# VITE_AUTH_BASE=/auth

# The Google client id + secret are SERVER-side secrets for the Pages Functions — never put them
# here. Set them on the Cloudflare Pages project (production) and in `.dev.vars` (local dev).
# See .dev.vars.example.
